    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> baby plum tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>fennel seeds</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> and grind (or chop if you don't have a pestle and mortar) to a fine powder</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-king-prawn-crab-tomato-and-fennel-linguine/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halved tomatoes</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> ground fennel seeds</strong> (not a fan of aniseed? Only add a little!) and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until the tomatoes have softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-king-prawn-crab-tomato-and-fennel-linguine/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> </strong>pasta<strong> </strong>for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat) or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the pasta<strong> </strong>and return to the pot, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-king-prawn-crab-tomato-and-fennel-linguine/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes have softened, increase the heat to medium-high</p><p>Drain then add your <strong>king prawns</strong> and <strong>tomato paste </strong>to the pan with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min or until cooked through</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-king-prawn-crab-tomato-and-fennel-linguine/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the prawns are cooked, add your <strong>crab meat</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[260ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened to a pasta sauce-like consistency \u2013 this is your <strong>fiery tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-king-prawn-crab-tomato-and-fennel-linguine/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> until you end up with a pile of cheese shavings</p><p>Grate any <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-king-prawn-crab-tomato-and-fennel-linguine/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained pasta </strong>and <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>to the fiery tomato sauce and gently stir together</p><p>Cook for 1 min further until the sauce begins to stick to the pasta \u2013 this is your<strong> fiery king prawn, crab, tomato & fennel pasta</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fiery-king-prawn-crab-tomato-and-fennel-linguine/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> fiery king prawn, crab, tomato & fennel pasta </strong>topped with <strong>chopped basil</strong> and<strong> Italian hard cheese shavings</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and drizzle with some <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
